description: From out- +‎ ask. Cognate with Old Frisian utaskia (“to outask”), Danish udæske (“to challenge”).

verbs.description: outask (third-person singular simple present outasks, present participle outasking, simple past and past participle outasked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To ask or proclaim for the last time.
(transitive) To announce or publish the banns of marriage of (a couple) in church for the third time.
